      "author": "Anti-Warlock",
      "description": "## VaultRelay 0.7.0\r\n\r\nVaultRelay helps Obsidian users prepare long-form Markdown notes for publishing without moving their vault.\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n- Preview long-form Markdown articles before publishing\r\n- Inspect headings, paragraphs, images, lists, and code blocks\r\n- Generate publish-ready image cards for social platforms\r\n- Export cards locally without uploading notes to a server\r\n- Support local images and remote image links such as OSS URLs\r\n- Keep the entire publishing workflow local-first\r\n\r\n### Privacy\r\n\r\nVaultRelay does not upload your notes to a VaultRelay server.\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nDownload `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css`.\r\n\r\nPlace them inside:\r\n\r\n`.obsidian/plugins/vault-relay/`\r\n\r\nThen restart Obsidian and enable VaultRelay under Community plugins.",
